Add a table footnote

Source: R/table_parts.R
tab_footnote.Rd

Add a footnote with a glyph attached to the targeted cells, rows, or columns.

tab_footnote(data, footnote, location)

Arguments

data

a table object that is created using the gt() function.
footnote

text to be used in the footnote.
location

the cell or set of cells to be associated with the footnote. Supplying an object with the data_cells() helper function is a useful way to specify the cell that is associated with the footnote.

Value

an object of class gt_tbl.

See also

[data_cells()] as a useful helper function for targeting the cell associated with the footnote.

Other table-part creation/modification functions: gt_preview, gt, tab_boxhead_panel, tab_heading, tab_options, tab_source_note, tab_stub_block, tab_stubhead_caption, tab_style

Examples

# Add a footnote that is in
# reference to a single table cell
gt(mtcars, rownames_to_stub = TRUE) %>%
  tab_footnote(
    footnote = "Massive hp.",
    location = data_cells(
      row = "Maserati Bora",
      column = "hp"))
